    <div class="alpheios-lex-entry" lemma-id="n9412" body-key="α">
          <b><span class="alpheios-lex-greek" lang="grc">φθέγγομαι</span></b> , fut. <span class="alpheios-lex-greek" lang="grc">φθέγξομαι</span>, aor. <span class="alpheios-lex-greek" lang="grc">ἐφθεγξάμην</span>, subj. <span class="alpheios-lex-greek" lang="grc">φθέγξομαι</span>: <span class="alpheios-lex-gloss">utter a sound, speak out</span>, cf.
            <span class="alpheios-lex-greek" lang="grc">φθογγή, φθόγγος</span>. Since the verb
          merely designates the effect upon the ear, it may be joined with a
          more specific word, <span class="alpheios-lex-greek" lang="grc">ἐφθέγγοντο
            καλεῦντες</span>, called <span class="alpheios-lex-gloss">aloud</span>, <i><span class="en">Od. 10.229</span></i>, <i><span class="en">Il.
            21.192</span></i>, <span class="alpheios-lex-greek" lang="grc">341; φθεγγομένου.. κάρη
            κονίῃσιν ἐμίχθη</span>, while the voice still
            <span class="alpheios-lex-gloss">sounded</span>, <i><span class="en">Il. 10.457</span></i>,
            <i><span class="en">Od. 22.329</span></i>.</div> <div class="alpheios-lex-footnotes en"> </div>
    <div class="alpheios-lex-alph-source">From <u>
            <u>A Homeric Dictionary</u>
        </u> (Georg Autenrieth, New York, Harper and Brothers, 1891) </div>
